main event: Multiple unidentified flying objects were observed on radar and visually by civilian and military witnesses in the Kansas City, Missouri area in 1957.
interesting points: The objects moved rapidly across the radar scope and then disappeared, with no sound detected.
One sighting involved two white objects, one with a trail, that were observed for 10-15 seconds.
Another sighting involved two bright spots in the sky that were moving in a straight line at a very rapid speed.
The reports were submitted to various military commands, including the 25th Air Division, Ent AFB, and the Air Technical Intelligence Center.
The conclusions were generally that there was insufficient data to identify the objects, with some speculation that they could have been aircraft or meteors.
sighted object: unidentified flying objects, including round objects, bright spots, and objects with trails
